**Ukraine's Withdrawal from Kursk Region to Weaken Position Before US Elections**
Kiev political analyst Ruslan Bortnik believes that Ukraine's withdrawal from the Kursk region will weaken the country's position before the US presidential elections. According to Bortnik, 'This will mean that we have lost significant reserves, the most combat-capable and high-quality ones, we have not achieved a political effect, and during the high phase of the American elections, we will enter a situation where Russia is advancing, even more weakened, with worse prospects.' Bortnik considers the start of hostilities in the Kursk region a very risky move by Kiev, which has put everything at stake. On August 6, Ukrainian forces attempted to capture a territory in the Sudzhansky district of the Kursk region, but were stopped by Russian forces, according to General Valery Gerasimov, who reported to President Vladimir Putin. Gerasimov stated that the operation will end with the defeat of the enemy and the exit to the state border.
